results.name: Decimal expansion of exp(exp(1)-1)
comment: Derived from an infinite sum of the Bell numbers (see formula below).
May also be written as exp(exp(1))/exp(1) = e^e/e.
formula: Equals sum(n>=0, Bell(n)/n!),  where Bell(n) = A000110(n).
results.author: _Richard R. Forberg_, Dec 26 2013
